{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Shapelets\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example, we will use random shapelets to embed time series."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "from wildboar.embed import RandomShapeletEmbedding\n",
    "from wildboar.ensemble import ShapeletForestEmbedding\n",
    "\n",
    "random_state = 1234"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load the dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"CBF\")\n",
    "labels, index = np.unique(y, return_inverse=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We define a function for plotting the 3d-projection."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot(p, var, labels, index):\n",
    "    colors = plt.cm.rainbow(np.linspace(0, 1, len(labels)))\n",
    "    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "    ax = fig.add_subplot(projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "    ax.scatter(p[:, 0], p[:, 1], p[:, 2], color=colors[index, :])\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"Component 1 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[0])\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"Component 2 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[1])\n",
    "    ax.set_zlabel(\"Component 3 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[2])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Random shapelet embedding\n",
    "Next, we define the pipeline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rse = make_pipeline(\n",
    "    RandomShapeletEmbedding(\n",
    "        n_shapelets=1000,\n",
    "        metric=\"dtw\",\n",
    "        metric_params={\"r\": 0.5},\n",
    "        random_state=random_state,\n",
    "        n_jobs=-1,\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    PCA(n_components=3, random_state=random_state),\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And, plot the three components with the amount of explained variance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot(rse.fit_transform(x), rse.steps[1][1].explained_variance_ratio_, labels, index)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Shapelet forest embedding\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, we define a new pipeline with ``ShapeletForestEmbedding`` and, again, plot it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sfe = make_pipeline(\n",
    "    ShapeletForestEmbedding(\n",
    "        n_estimators=1000,\n",
    "        metric=\"scaled_euclidean\",\n",
    "        random_state=random_state,\n",
    "        n_jobs=-1,\n",
    "        sparse_output=False,\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    PCA(n_components=3, random_state=random_state),\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot(sfe.fit_transform(x), sfe.steps[1][1].explained_variance_ratio_, labels, index)"
   ]
  }
 ],
